<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="119" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,1158,2011]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,582,1770,1795]" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[749,834,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Fig. 90</figureCitation>
) moderately produced posteriorly; posterior margin broadly convex, with median trapezoidal emargination bordered by small projection and with central triangular notch. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[389,473,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 85 – 97" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1860,1883]" captionTargetBox="[152,1423,327,1824]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[152,1435,321,1824]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 85 – 97. (85 – 88) Apogonalia sanguinipes (Van Duzee, 1907), female: 85, dorsal habitus; 86, sternite VII, ventral view; 87, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 88, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. (89 – 91) A. stali (Signoret, 1855), female: 89, dorsal habitus; 90, sternite VII, ventral view; 91, sternite VIII, dorsal view. (92 – 97) A. woodruffi Young, 1977, female: 92, dorsal habitus; 93, left forewing, lateral view; 94, face; 95, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 96, sternite VIII, anterior view; 97, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035602/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">Fig. 91</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with arch-shaped sclerotized plate; anterior margin of plate broadly convex; posterior margin narrowly concave, sinuous, with small and narrow median notch. Pygofer similar to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Signoret" baseAuthorityYear="1855" box="[185,334,1915,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interrupta">
<emphasis box="[185,334,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">A. interrupta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula I, in ventral view, similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Young" authorityYear="1977" box="[875,1007,1915,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="imitatrix">
<emphasis box="[875,1007,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">A. imitatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[1305,1429,1915,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[1305,1429,1915,1938]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[473,595,1951,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis box="[473,595,1951,1974]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="119">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; teeth, on median portion of blade, very prominent, 1.5 to 2 times longer than high; preapical prominence approximately aligned to anteapical tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
